programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 350 - Dynamite Fighting Show 20 Part 2
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Dynamite Fighting Show 20 part 2 from Bucharest Romania with a night of Kickboxing action. Starting off in the heavyweight division, Poland's Dominik Jedrejczyk takes on Romania's Claudiu Badoi in a David versus Goliath fight. Next up, Stefan Orza and Eduard Gafencu look to give fans a fight of the night. In two heavyweight matchups, Florin Ivanoaie faces Cristian Ristea and Ionut Iancu faces Sebastian Cozmanca.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 351 - KOK 103 World Series Tallinn Part 1
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents King of Kings 103 part 1 from Tallinn, Estonia. Kicking things off tonight Lithuanian Gedminas Justinas takes on Moldova's Sergei Cheles. In back to back female boxing events, Ernesta Kareckaite faces the more experienced Sigrid Kapanen and Aleksandra Dzhikaeva gets in the ring with Karolina Arm. Making his pro debut, Romualdas Auga takes on Aleksandrs Cerkesov.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 352 - KOK 103 World Series Tallinn Part 2
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents King of Kings 103 part 2 from Tallinn, Estonia. In a welterweight Grand Prix, Raimondas Avlasevicius faces Roman Jarysh in the first semi-final fight and in the second semi-final fight Dzianis Makouski joins Marko Sults in the ring with the winner moving on to the Grand Prix finals in the co-main event. Also in this episode, in a very evenly matched bout, Aleh Moshnin and Henry Rohtla face off in the ring.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 353 - KOK 103 World Series Tallinn Part 3
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents King of Kings 103 part 3 from Tallinn, Estonia. In tonight's episode in a middleweight bout Richardas Kulis of Lithuania fights Aleksei Larin from Estonia. In a bantamweight championship female fight, Ilona Wojda and Astrid Grents battle it out for the title. Also Ukranian Volodymyr Hynzhu faces Estonia's Hendrik Themas.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 354 - Fighters Only 15th Annual World Mixed Martial Arts Awards
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Fighters Only 15th Annual World Mixed Martial Arts Awards hosted by Chael Sonnen and honoring Ken Shamrock. These awards honor exceptional performance in various aspects of MMA including: Upset of the Year, Comback of the Year, Ring card Girl of the Year, Gym of the Year, Female and Male Fighter of the Year, Knockout of the Year and Fight of the Year.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 375 - KOK 105 Riga Part 2
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents King of Kings part 2 from Riga, Latvia. Starting us off Jakub Kwasniewski and Eduard Mishin battle it out in kickboxing contest. In the co-main event, Guillermo Blokland of the Netherlands faces Vjaceslavs Teless of Latvia and in the main event Poland's Michal Walczak and Latvia's Kristaps Zyle vie for the KOK European Light Heavyweight Championship in a Title fight.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 451 - Up Next Fighting 13 part 2
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Up Next Fighting 13 part 2 from the Commerce Hotel and Casino in Southern California. Starting off in the bantamweight division, Jonathan Powell steps into the cage with veteran grappler Will Holguin. In a featherweight bout, striker Jonny O'Neill takes on wrestler Eudardo Zarate with the winner moving on to a title opportunity. Also watch as Adam Garcia and Zachary Kraschinsky take to the ring in a lightweight bout. With two titles on the line in the featured bout, the rising star UNF Featherweight title and the California State featherweight title in the rising stars division, Stone Lavelle and his opponient Sean Crenshaw battle it out for the two belts.

programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents KOK '84 World Series from Vilnius Lithuania part 2. In the main event Lithuanians Zygimantas Ramaska and Vitoldas Jagelo face one another in an MMA Bushido battle with at title on the line.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 257 - Shamrock FC 334
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Shamrock Fighting Championship out of the Ameristar Casino in St. Charles, MO. In this event Austin Miller faces Arvin Mills in the cage, Arnez Ferguson takes on Pat Vega in a kickboxing bout and in a female match, Livvy Pecher takes on Lora Campbell. Also Jason Gavril faces Isaac Dancy and Nico Alcaraz takes on Todd Madden in the middleweight division. In the Co-Main event Devin Anderson takes on Aushton Elleby Midkiff and in the main event Jeremiah Curtright with a 3 fight win streak takes on Zack Davis with a 4 fight win streak.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 259 - KOK 94 Tallinn Part 1
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents King of Kings 94 World Series from Tallinn, Estonia part 1. Aleh Moshin from Belarus takes on Karl Margus Haud out of Estonia and Edvinas Bubelis (Lithuania) faces Sergei Strinza (Estonia). Also, powerhouse Volodymyr Hynzju from Ukraine takes on Aleksey Larin from Estonia.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 260 - KOK 94 Tallinn Part 2
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents King of Kings 94 World Series from Tallinn, Estonia part 2. Watch as the first ever KOK women's bantamweight world championship title is on the line. In the semi-finals Estonians Sigrid Kapanen and Astrid Johanna Grents fight to move on and Italian Ludovica Ciarpaglini faces Polish Ilona Woijda to see who will move on to the Grand Prix final match and have a chance at the title.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 255 - KOK’84 World Series, Vilnius part 1
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents KOK '84 World Series from Vilnius Lithuania part 1. In a battle between Lithuanian fighters, Zygimantas Kidikas making his pro debut goes up against his 2-0 opponent Ovidijus Pocius. Watch as Aleh Moshin (Belarus) faces Samuelis Sorochovas (Lithuania), Osvaladas Fedorovic takes on the less experienced Aurimas Krukauskas in a battle between Lithuanian fighters and Vladislav Shatunskui (Poland) battles against Gustas Dimsa (Lithuania). In addition Polish fighter Hubert Dylewski takes on Lithuanian Jan Naus in a very evenly matched fight.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 256 - KOK’84 World Series, Vilnius Part 2
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents KOK '84 World Series from Vilnius Lithuania part 2. In this episode, watch as Ukrainian Volodymyr Hynzhu takes on Lithuanian Raimondas Avlasevicius, Finn Larsen (Ireland) goes up against the more experienced Nauris Lukosiunas (Lithuania) and Oleskil Mykhailo 9-0 (Ukraine) faces Henrikas Viksraitis 43-7(Lithuania). In the main event Lithuanians Zygimantas Ramaska and Vitoldas Jagelo face one another in an MMA Bushido battle with at title on the line.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 257 - Shamrock FC 334
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Shamrock Fighting Championship out of the Ameristar Casino in St. Charles, MO. In this event Austin Miller faces Arvin Mills in the cage, Arnez Ferguson takes on Pat Vega in a kickboxing bout and in a female match, Livvy Pecher takes on Lora Campbell. Also Jason Gavril faces Isaac Dancy and Nico Alcaraz takes on Todd Madden in the middleweight division. In the Co-Main event Devin Anderson takes on Aushton Elleby Midkiff and in the main event Jeremiah Curtright with a 3 fight win streak takes on Zack Davis with a 4 fight win streak.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 258 - UFA Presents the Fighter's Only World MMA Awards XIII
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents the 13th annual Fighter's Only 2021 World MMA Awards from Worre Studios in Las Vegas, hosted by Chael Sonnen. Presentations by Dave Farra, Jessy Jess, Doggface208, Emily Whitmire, Cassie Scherbo, Jay Hieron, Dan Henderson, Kayla Harrison, Mackenzie Dern, and more.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 259 - KOK 94 Tallinn Part 1
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents King of Kings 94 World Series from Tallinn, Estonia part 1. Young Estonian fighters Stanislav Teniugin and Siim Viljus battle under KOK Kickboxing rules. Aleh Moshin from Belarus takes on Karl Margus Haud out of Estonia and Edvinas Bubelis (Lithuania) faces Sergei Strinza (Estonia). Also, powerhouse Volodymyr Hynzju from Ukraine takes on Aleksey Larin from Estonia.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 260 - KOK 94 Tallinn Part 2
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents King of Kings 94 World Series from Tallinn, Estonia part 2. Watch as the first ever KOK women's bantamweight world championship title is on the line. In some intense all-female matchups each fighter is vying to move on to the finals for a chance at the title. In the semi-finals Estonians Sigrid Kapanen and Astrid Johanna Grents fight to move on and Italian Ludovica Ciarpaglini faces Polish Ilona Woijda to see who will move on to the Grand Prix final match and have a chance at the title.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 261 - KOK 94 Tallinn Part 3
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents King of Kings 94 World Series from Tallinn, Estonia part 3. Watch as Canadian Mohammed Shushan faces Jevgeni "Zora XXL" Ravlusevits of Estonia and Dzmitry Varats (Belarus) takes on Ott Remmer (Estonia).

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 262 - Shamrock FC 335
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Shamrock 335 from Ameristar Casino St Charles. Watch as Pat Gordon takes on Adam Stone, Stanton Ketcherside faces Jerry Ing, Matt Tinker battles it out against James Yarbrough, Kevin Mueller faces Trevon Crawford and Tavae Lewis faces Josh Weston In the co-main event in a kickboxing bout, Ian Zarvos faces Cody Naucke and in the main event Josh Augustin returns to the cage after a long layoff to take on blackbelt Thomas Thatcher.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 263 - SFT 30 - Predador vs Manchinha
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents SFT 30 from Brazil. Denis Araujo with 6 KO's meets Jose Reborn Alexandre in the cage for a fierce MMA bout. In a compelling matchup, Paulo Pizzo takes on the much younger Fernando "ben 10" Lourenco and in the lightweight division #1 ranked Felipe Buakaw takes on #2 Marcio Velaminho. In the main event Wellington Predador faces Thiago Manchinha in an exciting matchup.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 259 - KOK 94 Tallinn Part 1
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents King of Kings 94 World Series from Tallinn, Estonia part 1. Young Estonian fighters Stanislav Teniugin and Siim Viljus battle under KOK Kickboxing rules. Aleh Moshin from Belarus takes on Karl Margus Haud out of Estonia and Edvinas Bubelis (Lithuania) faces Sergei Strinza (Estonia). Also, powerhouse Volodymyr Hynzju from Ukraine takes on Aleksey Larin from Estonia.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 260 - KOK 94 Tallinn Part 2
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents King of Kings 94 World Series from Tallinn, Estonia part 2. Watch as the first ever KOK women's bantamweight world championship title is on the line. In some intense all-female matchups each fighter is vying to move on to the finals for a chance at the title. In the semi-finals Estonians Sigrid Kapanen and Astrid Johanna Grents fight to move on and Italian Ludovica Ciarpaglini faces Polish Ilona Woijda to see who will move on to the Grand Prix final match and have a chance at the title.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 261 - KOK 94 Tallinn Part 3
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents King of Kings 94 World Series from Tallinn, Estonia part 3. Watch as Canadian Mohammed Shushan faces Jevgeni "Zora XXL" Ravlusevits of Estonia and Dzmitry Varats (Belarus) takes on Ott Remmer (Estonia).

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 262 - Shamrock FC 335
programme.desc: United Fight Alliance presents Shamrock 335 from Ameristar Casino St Charles. Watch as Pat Gordon takes on Adam Stone, Stanton Ketcherside faces Jerry Ing, Matt Tinker battles it out against James Yarbrough, Kevin Mueller faces Trevon Crawford and Tavae Lewis faces Josh Weston In the co-main event in a kickboxing bout, Ian Zarvos faces Cody Naucke and in the main event Josh Augustin returns to the cage after a long layoff to take on blackbelt Thomas Thatcher.

programme.title: United Fight Alliance - UFA 263 - SFT 30 - Predador vs Manchinha

In a compelling matchup, Paulo Pizzo takes on the much younger Fernando "ben 10" Lourenco and in the lightweight division #1 ranked Felipe Buakaw takes on #2 Marcio Velaminho. In the main event Wellington Predador faces Thiago Manchinha in an exciting matchup.

programme.desc: When Union spies steal Johnnie Gray's (Buster Keaton) beloved locomotive, the General, he pursues them with the aid of his fiancée, Annabelle Lee (Marion Mack) straight through enemy lines. One of the most revered comedies of the silent era.

programme.title: Officers
programme.desc: Epic Soviet era masterpiece depicting the unshakable bonds of love, friendship & duty amid the horror of war. Two friends, both officers, are in love with the same woman. Through the Russian Civil War to WWII, they fight and love and die.

programme.title: The Southerner
programme.desc: In this rural drama, Zachary Scott is a Texan cotton picker who aspires to run his own farm and create a better life for his family, which includes two kids, his irritable granny (Beulah Bondi), and his beautiful wife (Betty Field). 3 Oscar nominations.

programme.title: Meet John Doe
programme.desc: A reporter, Ann Mitchell writes a fictitious column about someone named "John Doe" and convinces a homeless man 'Long John' Willoughby to impersonate this fictitious character so she can keep her job.

programme.title: 雪夫人絵図: Portrait of Madame Yuki
programme.desc: Young servant girl Hamako has just started working for her personal heroine, Madame Yuki. Her romanticized view of the Madame is broken immediately, as she is introduced with a list of the Madame's personal problems.

programme.title: Royal Wedding
programme.desc: American sibling song-and-dance team (Fred Astaire and Jane Powell) are in London when all of England is in a tizzy over the nuptials of the Princess and Prince. Ellen falls head over heels for a dashing Lord (Peter Lawford).

programme.title: The King of Kings
programme.desc: Jesus Christ faces religious and political oppression during his ministry and the days before his death and resurrection.

programme.title: The Klansman
programme.desc: A small Southern town erupts in violence when a local sheriff confronts the Klan, exposing deep-seated hatred and a fight for justice.

programme.title: Captain Pugwash
programme.desc: Hurrah for Captain Horatio Pugwash! As he sets out on adventures on his fine ship The Black Pig with his motley crew. Sadly, a storm rolled in and destroyed a part of the ship leaving the captain and most of crew lost at sea.

programme.title: Captain Pugwash
programme.desc: Cut Throat Jake- the captain’s worst enemy, was locked away in the town’s jail. As Captain Pugwash and the crew were doing target practice, one of their cannon’s blew a hole in the side of the prison. Cut Throat Jake was free!

programme.title: Captain Pugwash
programme.desc: Captain Pugwash was lost and stuck at sea and the ship had drifted into the sea monster’s domain! Suddenly, The Black Pig is attacked by a scary sea monster, but Tom the Cabin Boy had a plan to escape and save the crew.

programme.title: Captain Pugwash
programme.desc: One night, there was a mouse in the crew’s quarters. Captain Pugwash prepared his men to find and get rid of the mouse. But what they didn’t know was that Cut Throat Jake and his band of pirates were sneaking onto The Black Pig!

programme.title: Captain Pugwash
programme.desc: Captain Pugwash had decided to decorate his ship, ordering his crew to buy a bunch of paint. The captain wanted a pillar removed in his quarters, ignoring his shipmate’s concerns, the pillar was moved and the whole ship fell apart.

programme.title: Captain Pugwash
programme.desc: Captain Pugwash was wanted for piracy, he was captured and thrown into the town’s dungeon. Tom and the pirates set off to rescue their captain at low tide, drilling a hole through the wall.

programme.title: Captain Pugwash
programme.desc: Pugwash and his shipmates had found an island to eat for the annual pirate picnic party. Tom threw all the rubbish into the chest and buried it in the sand. Suddenly, Cut Throat Jake came ashore! He opened the treasure chest only to find rubbish.

programme.title: Captain Pugwash
programme.desc: Captain Pugwash went out fishing one day, only to be swallowed by a giant fish! But he wasn’t alone in the sea creature’s belly, Cut Throat Jake was stuck inside too. Pugwash and Jake fought and were eventually spat up by the fish.

programme.title: Captain Pugwash
programme.desc: The crew came to Pugwash with a complaint, leaving The Captain to set up some new rules. The pirates were fed up with Pugwash as their leader and kicked him off the ship, and Tom joined him. But soon the shipmates started feeling lost without them both.

programme.title: Captain Pugwash
programme.desc: Captain Pugwash put away all his money in the bank, but his crew needed to be paid. Pugwash said he didn’t have any money, so the pirates decided to rob a bank. However, they ended up stealing Pugwash’s money, and they used every penny.

programme.title: Our Hospitality
programme.desc: A man returns to his Appalachian homestead. On the trip, he falls for a young woman. The only problem is her family has vowed to kill every member of his family.

programme.title: The Penalty
programme.desc: A deformed criminal mastermind plans to loot the city of San Francisco as well as revenge himself on the doctor who mistakenly amputated his legs.

programme.title: Ben-Hur: A Tale of the Christ
programme.desc: Judah Ben-Hur seeks revenge against his childhood friend, now a Roman conqueror, after enduring slavery and loss. In his quest for justice and reconciliation, he finds redemption and unexpected twists of fate.

programme.title: God's Gun
programme.desc: A priest and his twin brother take turns defending a small town from the vicious Clayton gang.

programme.title: The Docks of New York
programme.desc: A blue-collar worker on New York’s depressed waterfront finds his life changed after he saves a woman attempting suicide.

programme.title: Spring on Zarechnaya Street
programme.desc: A newly appointed Russian literature teacher develops a strong connection with one of her flagging students.

programme.title: D.W. Griffith's Abraham Lincoln
programme.desc: The film is a 1930 pre-code American biographical adaptation about Abraham Lincoln, directed by D. W. Griffith. This is also the first full-sound film of this Director.

programme.title: Pandora's Box
programme.desc: The rise and inevitable fall of an amoral but naive young woman whose insouciant eroticism inspires lust and violence in those around her.

programme.title: Johnny On The Spot
programme.desc: 1954, Johnny (Hugh McDermott) returns from a prison sentence to get the man who framed him.

programme.title: Cyrano de Bergerac
programme.desc: France, 1640: Cyrano, the charismatic swordsman-poet with the absurd nose, hopelessly loves the beauteous Roxane; she, in turn, confesses to Cyrano her love for the handsome but tongue-tied Christian. Remastered for 4K UHD.

programme.title: The Snows of Kilimanjaro
programme.desc: The life of Harry (Gregory Peck) a writer, flashes before his eyes as he lies dying near Mount Kilimanjaro. He is tended to by his traveling companion, Helen (Susan Hayward) and he recalls his first wife Cynthia (Ava Gardner). Remastered for 4K UHD.

programme.desc: Wilbur works in an old carnival and shows some gruesome things to the puplic. He covered his face because he had a sadistic father who burned his face. When he puts the mask on, everybody who looks on this mask commits suicide. He has created the Death-Mask.

programme.title: Hunting Season

programme.title: Exorcism in Utero

programme.title: American Terror Story

programme.title: Speed Catamarans GC32 - Episode 6
programme.desc: For its sixth season, the ultra-high performance one design catamarans, once again visited five top venues across the world. Each location selected particularly for its ideal weather conditions - stable winds and flat waters - perfect for the nimble GC32s to fly across the water at speeds of over 30 knots. Earlier in 2019, intensive discussions and decisions took place within the teams with many deciding to focus their efforts for the upcoming season, on the GC32 Racing Tour. This season the tour welcomed some new teams as well as many familiar regular GC32 crews. In total 12 teams from 9 different counties came together to take part in the 6th GC32 Racing Tour. Amongst them, some of the most well-known professional sailors in the world.

programme.title: H2O Racing: Aquabike World Championship - GP Spain - Ski
Facing Waves - Ep3 - Kayaking Ruka-Kuusamo, Finland
Facing Waves - Ep4 - Great Family Adventure - Columbus, Georgia - Freestyle Kayaking World Championships
programme.desc: Pro kayakers Nick Troutman and Emily Jackson and family head to the Freestyle Kayaking World Championships in Columbus, Georgia.

programme.title: Kite Masters - Episode 5
programme.desc: There are two elements that grabbed our attention during the 2020 Formula Kite Mixed Relay European Championships: the UK’s Connor Bainbridge and the Polish team.Along with his teammate Elli Aldridge, Connor managed to defend his European title. Meanwhile, the Polish team was the great surprise of the championship, having two out of their six teams qualifying to the gold fleet. After that, we will focus on the Kite venues hosting the hottest action from the kite events.We will discover why riders love these locations and what makes the International Kiteboarding Association so confident in the venues. Finally, we reencounter four-time world champion, Daniela Moroz, who shared some more golden Kiteboarding tips.

programme.title: Kite Masters - Episode 6
programme.desc: As we come to the end of the 2020 series, we'll take a look back over all the happenings earlier this season in the extreme world of kiteboarding as well as the transformation of the sport on the road to Paris 2024.Later on, we are set to find out what happened during the last event of the season, the 2020 KiteFoil European Championships taking place in Playa de las Burras, Gran Canaria, Spain. We end our journey travelling to the USA to meet one of the most popular riders in the world: Daniela Moroz.

programme.title: International Canoe Federation World Cup - Sprint 3 World Championships Szeged
programme.desc: Welcome to the Canoe Sprint World Championships 2019 celebrated in Szeged, Hungary! Today there are about 1,200 athletes racing from approximately 98 nations, meaning this is the biggest World Championships canoe sprint racing has ever seen. We're about to witness the fastest paddlers on the planet battle it out for medals, for World Championship glory, and to qualify for their country at the Tokyo 2020 Olympic Games. Enjoy the best moments at Szeged on the 2019 Sprint World Championships.

programme.title: International Canoe Federation World Cup - Slalom 1 World Cup Ljubljana
programme.desc: Ljubljana is the chosen scenery for the Slalom World Cup. The slovenian capital will bring the top kayakers who will navigate the whitewater course passing through a series of combination of upstream and downstream gates. The fastest to achieve this will become the champion of the World Cup. Find out now what will happen in Ljubljana in the exciting Slalom World Cup!

programme.title: Sailing To Tokyo - Episode 2
programme.desc: In this episode we are following the 2019 RSX European Championships. The 2019 RS:X Europeans and Youth European Championships which are being held on the island of Mallorca, Spain, is a record turn out for the RS:X Class with 333 confirmed entries from 43 different nations representing six different continents over five days of racing. This is not a challenge for the class and athletes alone, but also for the local host Club Nautic Arenal.

programme.title: Rolex New York Yacht Invitational Cup - Highlight
Speed Catamarans GC32 - Episode 6

programme.title: H2O Racing: Aquabike World Championship - GP Spain - Ski
Anchored in Paradise - Ep.6 - NIN - PAG
Atlantic Cup - Episode 2
programme.desc: The second leg of the race goes from New York City to New Port City, Rhode Island. There are two major challenges on this leg: one is getting out of New York Harbour, dealing with the tides and the thicker winds that come off the city, and the other is dealing with the commercial traffic, as it is one of the busiest ports in the world. How will the skippers manage?

programme.title: Gulf of Mexico
programme.desc: Beppe Faresin is an extreme kayaker with a dream: venturing into the Gulf of Mexico on a kayak. In this adventure, he will kayak his way through the Mexican lagoons and swamps to discover the wild nature of this unique country. Faresin is already famous for raising funds for UNICEF while paddling in rivers and oceans all over the world. Now, he faces a new challenge: crossing the Gulf of Mexico by himself. For almost 1500 km, this apparently fearless athlete will discover corners of Mexico otherwise unreachable by land. Follow his challenge navigating through the Gulf and find out what happens along the way.

programme.title: H2O Racing: Aquabike World Championship - GP Spain - Ski
Transat Panerai Classique
programme.desc: World Champion Kitesurfer and Nautical Channel host, Bruno Sroka travels to Martinique to welcome the gems of the sea from their Atlantic crossing. The Transat Panerai Classique 2015 is arriving to the Caribbean island. They departed from Lanzarote, in the Canary Islands, and after sailing 3.000nm these classic and historic sailing ships have endured the hardships of the ocean and are eager to arrive in first place for a well deserved victory. Witness some of the most extraordinary yachts ever built and have fun seeing Bruno take the sea on both a traditional Martinique Yoles boat and a Classic European one. Classic Boats, Turquoise Caribbean waters and world champion hosts... what more could we ask for? Enjoy the Transat Panerai Classique 2015 on Nautical Channel.

programme.title: Reaching Reality - Episode 1 - Origin
programme.desc: From under the Golden Gate Bridge down to the Santa Cruz Islands the three friends and their little boat are now heading south. However bad weather is on the horizon and signs that the film and the filmmaker are already thinking about abandoning ship are starting to leak through. After a long night of sea sickness, it’s time to face reality and see who’s going to stick around and who’s going to go.

programme.title: Formula Wing European Championships - Ep.1 - URLA
New York - Vendée Transatlantic Race
programme.desc: This single-handed yacht race will cross the Northern Atlantic through two symbolic cities: New York and Sables d’Olonne. The departure from the Big Apple represents a cosmopolitan crossroad of influences, as well as the cradle of the IMOCA Class, while the arrival in the Sables d’Olonne means landing in the Old Continent after days or weeks of harsh conditions.After crossing a risky and challenging course straight through the middle of the “iceberg alley”, the skippers will arrive in the heart of the Vendée Globe considered as the “Everest of the Sea”. The Transatlantic race is the final event of the IMOCA Globe Series and it allows racers to build their hard racing miles. It represents a further opportunity to reinforce its image as a marine region, thus it is an awaited event for all those sailors thinking about embarking on the Vendée Globe.Follow their journey from New York to Sables d’Olonne in New York – Vendée Transatlantic Race. Available on Nautical Channel.

programme.title: Facing Waves - Ep5 - Kayaking Ireland\'s West Coast
programme.desc: Ken Whiting explores the Republic of Ireland\'s West Coast and the adventures by kayak and foot along the Wild Atlantic Way.

programme.title: Facing Waves - Ep6 - Great Family Adventure - Banff and Lake Louise, Canada
programme.desc: Pro kayakers Nick Troutman, Emily Jackson and family try some winter activities on for size in beautiful Banff and Lake Louise, Canada.

programme.title: Discovering Watersports On Terceira
programme.desc: Terceira, on the Azores Islands, is a nautical sporting paradise for many. From pro surfers to passionate sailors, we dive into the lives of local athletes that are fortunate to call this island home.Discovering Watersports On Terceira joins athletes from different categories on their nautical challenges on their way to excellence. However, it also centers on the human aspect, checking on secret spots used by these water enthusiasts as well as lifestyle in the Azores Islands.Join us in their adventure, here on Nautical Channel.

programme.title: Endless Summer In Norfolk
programme.desc: Norfolk: population to just over 240,000 people and neighbour of the Chesapeake Bay is one of the top nautical destination for many enthusiasts in the USA. Holding a strong historical heritage and home to the largest naval base in the world, nautical sports are practiced regularly in this city in Virginia. Nautical Channel host Lucia Metzbauer heads to Virginia to discover Norfolk and what makes it so important in the nautical world. A port city on the Chesapeake Bay, bordering the Atlantic Ocean and countless rivers in its backyard, you just can't get away from the water. Discover some of the incredible 144 miles of coastline in the heart of Virginia with Lucia Metzbauer.Get ready to live an Endless Summer in Norfolk on Nautical Channel.

programme.title: Durban Extravaganza
programme.desc: Durban: a coastal city in eastern South Africa’s KwaZulu-Natal province known for its diverse influences and for hosting the Durban Extravaganza. The City of Durban and Durban Stars have brought the heat to the beautiful beachfront with the Surfing South Africa sanctioned Pro Surf Tour competition. Over 3 three days, the top 100 surfers gather in the South African city to participate in the hottest surfing competition of the African country.You can expect high-level competition with waves that are over 2-3 foot in Durban Extravaganza. Competing at the Bay of Plenty, surfers will surely dive in for plenty of action. A fanta-SEA for surf lovers!

programme.title: Nautical Adventure In A Landlocked Country
programme.desc: Switzerland: home to the Alps and important water competitions like the Bol d’Or Mirabaud, the most important inland lake regatta in the world. Today it becomes the chosen scenario for this Nautical Adventure in a Landlocked Country. From extreme wakeboarding to canoe polo, we will discover that, despite being located far from the sea, Switzerland has a vibrant nautical scene.Get ready to accompany Nautical Channel’s host, Lucia Metzbauer, as she goes wakeboarding with local Swiss pros, learns about the annual Match Race regatta, tries her hand at Stand-Up-Paddle, and discovers the little known sport of Canoe Polo! This country has much to offer, so don’t miss out on its beautiful scenery that will have you pack your bags to come visit on the first occasion.Nautical Adventure in a Landlocked Country reminds us that water sports can be practiced even in countries that do not border the ocean. An inland fanta-sea for those nautical intrepids that are looking for ways of widening their horizons. Welcome to the Alps.

programme.title: Jump On Board - Episode 8
programme.desc: We are sailing through Iraklia, one of the islands that make up the Cyclades in Greece. Our captain Deanna, skipper Giorgio, Dulce and Maria will take a nice swim in the harbour before exploring the island's caves. Are you coming with us?

programme.title: Jump On Board - Episode 9
programme.desc: Today we say goodbye to our skipper Giorgio, who is leaving us, and welcoming Marcos who will take us to Paros. As we approach the end of our trip, we start getting emotional and recall the best moments of this trip.

programme.title: Formula Wing European Championships - Ep.1 - URLA
New York - Vendée Transatlantic Race
programme.desc: This single-handed yacht race will cross the Northern Atlantic through two symbolic cities: New York and Sables d’Olonne. The departure from the Big Apple represents a cosmopolitan crossroad of influences, as well as the cradle of the IMOCA Class, while the arrival in the Sables d’Olonne means landing in the Old Continent after days or weeks of harsh conditions.After crossing a risky and challenging course straight through the middle of the “iceberg alley”, the skippers will arrive in the heart of the Vendée Globe considered as the “Everest of the Sea”. The Transatlantic race is the final event of the IMOCA Globe Series and it allows racers to build their hard racing miles. It represents a further opportunity to reinforce its image as a marine region, thus it is an awaited event for all those sailors thinking about embarking on the Vendée Globe.Follow their journey from New York to Sables d’Olonne in New York – Vendée Transatlantic Race. Available on Nautical Channel.

programme.title: Kite Masters - Episode 5
programme.desc: There are two elements that grabbed our attention during the 2020 Formula Kite Mixed Relay European Championships: the UK’s Connor Bainbridge and the Polish team.Along with his teammate Elli Aldridge, Connor managed to defend his European title. Meanwhile, the Polish team was the great surprise of the championship, having two out of their six teams qualifying to the gold fleet. After that, we will focus on the Kite venues hosting the hottest action from the kite events.We will discover why riders love these locations and what makes the International Kiteboarding Association so confident in the venues. Finally, we reencounter four-time world champion, Daniela Moroz, who shared some more golden Kiteboarding tips.

programme.title: Kite Masters - Episode 6
programme.desc: As we come to the end of the 2020 series, we'll take a look back over all the happenings earlier this season in the extreme world of kiteboarding as well as the transformation of the sport on the road to Paris 2024.Later on, we are set to find out what happened during the last event of the season, the 2020 KiteFoil European Championships taking place in Playa de las Burras, Gran Canaria, Spain. We end our journey travelling to the USA to meet one of the most popular riders in the world: Daniela Moroz.

programme.title: Anchored in Paradise - Ep.7 - NOVALJA - RAB
Atlantic Cup - Episode 3
programme.desc: Welcome back to this edition of the Atlantic Cup. It is time for the third and final leg of the competition, the inshore series. Dragon and Gryphon Solo 2 are tied for, and teams have added 4 extra crew, allowing them to push their boats around the tight courses in Naragannset Bay. Any mistake could be the difference between first and last. Who will become the winner in this edition?

programme.title: International Canoe Federation World Cup - Sprint 3 World Championships Szeged
programme.desc: Welcome to the Canoe Sprint World Championships 2019 celebrated in Szeged, Hungary! Today there are about 1,200 athletes racing from approximately 98 nations, meaning this is the biggest World Championships canoe sprint racing has ever seen. We're about to witness the fastest paddlers on the planet battle it out for medals, for World Championship glory, and to qualify for their country at the Tokyo 2020 Olympic Games. Enjoy the best moments at Szeged on the 2019 Sprint World Championships.

programme.title: FEI Dressage World Cup - Salzburg Competition
programme.desc: Welcome to Salzburg!The second leg of the Western European League inside the FEI Dressage World Cup takes place in the Austrian city. We are ready to see some of the very best horse and rider combinations in the sport and immerse in the city Mozart grew up in. Celebrating its 35th year, Dressage World Cup is the most distinguished individual competition in the international dressage calendar, rising at four leagues across the world: Western Europe, Central Europe, North America and Asia Pacific. The Western European League gathers together Europe's nine best dressage competitions, and, despite these challenging times, Salzburg has proved to be a safe destination where the exquisiteness of dressage will feel just like at home. Follow the Fei Dressage World Cup from Salzburg to find out what rider takes the upper hand in this competition.

programme.title: Cavalli a Roma - Best Moments
programme.desc: Cavalli a Roma mixes tradition with innovation, delighting the public with show jumping competitions, equestrian art and traditional shows that grasp both adults and children's attention. Now, on HorseTV you can revive all the emotions and best impressions of the 2020 edition.

programme.title: Campus Life Experience - Episode 6
programme.desc: In this new episode, we first realize the vet check to determine whether the horse is in good physical condition to take part in the competition. Once everything is fine with our horses, we check our rider's boots and then get a good night sleep as we will have to wake up at 6 for Manuel's class.

programme.title: Campus Life Experience - Episode 7
programme.desc: The educational program that lasted a week is finally reaching its end. Participants had their cell phones taken away and were given food, clothes and taught how to take care of their horses. Now, they are sad their adventure is over but share with us their final impressions for the week.

programme.desc: The Swedish capital of Stockholm is the host of the eighth leg of the Longines Global Champions Tour 2022: the international circuit that challenges top-riders from around the world in individual show jumping. As one of the hardest jump offs this season, who will make it to the top in Sweden? Watch the highlights of the Longines Global Champions Tour Stockholm Grand Prix!

programme.title: Event Rider Masters - Millstreet
programme.desc: For the fifth leg of the Event Rider Masters we head to the 'Land of the Horse' for the first time. Millstreet in Ireland is the chosen venue this time, and the Cross-Country Course in the adjoining Drishane Castle Demesne has quickly established itself as a favourite amongst the best riders of the world. Be part of the best moments of the competition at Millstreet.

programme.title: FEI Dressage European Championship - Riesenbeck - Individual Competition
FEI Dressage World Cup - Episode 1 - Salzburg
programme.desc: Welcome to Salzburg for the second leg of the FEI Dressage World Cup. We are in Austria to see some of the very best horse and rider combinations in the sport. Celebrating its 35th year, the FEI Dressage World Cup is the most distinguished individual competition in the international dressage calendar. Despite these challenging times and many events getting cancelled, Salzburg has proved herself a safe host to bring back the sport. Relive the highlights of the competition in Salzburg in the FEI Dressage World Cup of 2021.

programme.title: FEI Rides Magazine - Episode 2: Stories from the Stud
programme.desc: This week Ride seeks out the scorching sands of Kuwait where the Arabian Horse reigns supreme, skims the surf on the Emerald Isle with the Connemara Ponies of Cashel Bay Stud and recognises the dressage stars of the future at the home of Germany’s Olympic Gold Medalist Sonke Rothenberger.

programme.title: FEI Rides Magazine - Episode 3: Horses & Heritage
programme.desc: This week Ride travels back in time on the UK’s waterways aboard one of the last remaining horse drawn Barges. We fly high in California with Karrie Rufer, star of the Longines FEI Jumping World Cup North American League, step out with the sure-footed shires as they “Relay” acrross rural England, and witness the spectacle that is the dancing Spanish stallions at the Royal Andalusian School in Jerez.

programme.title: Event Rider Masters - Millstreet
programme.desc: For the fifth leg of the Event Rider Masters we head to the 'Land of the Horse' for the first time. Millstreet in Ireland is the chosen venue this time, and the Cross-Country Course in the adjoining Drishane Castle Demesne has quickly established itself as a favourite amongst the best riders of the world. Be part of the best moments of the competition at Millstreet.

programme.title: German High Goal Polo Championship - German High Goal Polo Championship
programme.desc: The German Polo Tour has been the top polo league in Germany since 2010. Now, rivalling teams will have to compete in the Prussian & Country Club Berlin-Brandenburg for the Cup. The final between Carfactory and Riller & Schmauck is now on. Enjoy the competition and follow the top level of german polo in Horse TV.

programme.title: Jumping International Bordeaux - Grand Prix Land Rover
programme.desc: The CSI5*W Grand Prix Land Rover Trophée is one of the most awaited competitions in the Jumping International de Bordeaux. With a height of 1.60m, it is one of the toughest tests in the French event. Riders will have to show their perseverance, effort and speed in the obstacle course in order to get a spot in the podium.Relieve the best moments of the Grand Prix Land Rover 2019 edition.

programme.title: Longines Global Champions Tour - Episode 17 - Prague
Dressage Season Review - Review
programme.desc: The Grand Prix at the final in Gothenburg will be disputed with Freestyle with music, and it will be extremely difficult. Only the best riders of the four leagues have made it this far and they have been giving their all throughout the entire season. Relive the best moments of the 2018/2019 Dressage World Cup season.
